.TH DICTIONARY "1" "December 2025" "dictionary 202409241930-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dictionary \- Thesaurus and dictionary lookup using Free Dictionary API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dictionary
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,WORD\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dictionary
is an enhanced dictionary and thesaurus tool that provides comprehensive word information including definitions, synonyms, antonyms, etymology, phonetics, and usage examples. It uses the Free Dictionary API (dictionaryapi.dev) to fetch word data and provides both terminal and optional GUI output.
.PP
The script features search history tracking, word list management, random word lookup, and optional audio pronunciation playback. Results can be displayed in graphical dialogs (yad/zenity) or formatted terminal output with color support.
.PP
Unlike the simpler
.B define
command, dictionary offers more comprehensive linguistic information and word management features making it suitable for writers, students, and language learners.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B dictionary [word]
Display all available information for the word (definitions, synonyms, antonyms, phonetics, examples, origin)
.TP
.B dictionary definition [word]
Show only definitions for the word organized by part of speech
.TP
.B dictionary example [word]
Display example sentences and usage of the word in context
.TP
.B dictionary phonetic [word]
Show phonetic pronunciation text and audio URLs, optionally play audio if sox is installed
.TP
.B dictionary synonym [word]
List synonyms (words with similar meaning)
.TP
.B dictionary antonym [word]
List antonyms (words with opposite meaning)
.TP
.B dictionary origin [word]
Display etymology and word origin information
.TP
.B dictionary history [clear]
Show recent word lookups from search history, or clear history with 'clear' argument
.TP
.B dictionary save-word [word] [list_name]
Save word to a named list for later reference
.TP
.B dictionary list-words [list_name]
Display saved words from specified list, or show all lists if no name given
.TP
.B dictionary random
Look up a random word (useful for vocabulary building)
