.SH API INTEGRATION
.SS Free Dictionary API (dictionaryapi.dev)
Primary API for comprehensive word data. Returns JSON with:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Word definitions organized by part of speech (noun, verb, adjective, etc.)
.IP \(bu 2
Multiple meanings per part of speech
.IP \(bu 2
Phonetic pronunciation text and audio URLs
.IP \(bu 2
Example sentences demonstrating usage
.IP \(bu 2
Synonyms and antonyms
.IP \(bu 2
Etymology and word origin information
.RE
.PP
Default endpoint: https://api.dictionaryapi.dev/api/v2/entries/en/{word}
.PP
API Response Structure:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B word
\- The word queried
.IP \(bu 2
.B phonetics[]
\- Pronunciation data (text, audio URL)
.IP \(bu 2
.B meanings[]
\- Array of meanings by part of speech
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B partOfSpeech
\- noun, verb, adjective, etc.
.IP \(bu 2
.B definitions[]
\- Array of definitions with examples
.IP \(bu 2
.B synonyms[]
\- Words with similar meaning
.IP \(bu 2
.B antonyms[]
\- Words with opposite meaning
.RE
.IP \(bu 2
.B origin
\- Etymology and historical development
.RE
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
Results are formatted for readability:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
# definitions for word
1. First definition with detailed explanation
2. Second definition for different context
3. Third definition for additional usage

# synonyms for word
similar, equivalent, comparable, alike

# antonyms for word
opposite, contrary, different, dissimilar

# phonetics audio for word
https://api.dictionaryapi.dev/media/pronunciations/en/word.mp3

# example usage of word
The word was used in various contexts throughout history.
Usage evolved to encompass modern meanings.

# origins of word
Etymology: From Latin origin, through Middle English...
.EE
.RE
.SH GUI INTEGRATION
When running in a graphical environment (X11 display available, not SSH), dictionary automatically uses GUI dialogs for better readability.
.SS Supported GUI Tools
.TP
.B yad
Yet Another Dialog - modern dialog replacement with rich text formatting (preferred)
.TP
.B zenity
Display GTK+ dialogs from command line (fallback option)
.PP
GUI dialogs require:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
X11 display available ($DISPLAY environment variable set)
.IP \(bu 2
Not connected via SSH (no $SSH_CONNECTION)
.IP \(bu 2
yad or zenity installed
.RE
.PP
If GUI requirements aren't met, output automatically falls back to formatted terminal display with color support.
.PP
To force terminal output even in GUI environments:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Set CONSOLE_APP=true environment variable
.IP \(bu 2
Use --raw option to disable colors
.RE
